      "writtenOn": "2020-07-10T18:05:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If the only map states we need to check against are \"mapped\" or \"not mapped\", could we just have an \"isMapped() { return fMapPtr !\u003d nullptr; }\" ?\n\n(The only place I could find that checks for Pending is an assert in the other CL, in a piece of code I\u0027d like to remove :) )\n\nActually, could we have the map callback simply remove its buffer from the busy list when the callback is called? Then we could remove this function altogether.\n\nAs you point out, they should be removed in the order they were added, so even though we\u0027ll have to iterate to find which one to remove, it\u0027s likely going to be the first one in the list anyway.",
      "revId": "f6d4a4eeb224d78f23a90d479472e7b31dc86683",
